======================================================================
PART 7: G(z) at algebraic points
======================================================================

  G(z) = 1/(1-z) + a1*z/(1-z)^2 + a2*z*(1+z)/(1-z)^3

  Known: G(1/2) = H + 1 + 2*a2
         G(1/3) = 3/2 + 3a1/4 + 3a2/2

  G(-1) [formal]: 1/2 - a1/4 + 0 = (2-a1)/4
  This is the alternating-sum generating function!
