PART 10: The constraint b0 + b1 + b2 = 1 in mod arithmetic
======================================================================

  b0 + b1 + b2 = I(0) = 1 (always)
  Mod 2: b0+b1+b2 = 1, so an odd number of {b0,b1,b2} are odd
  Mod 3: b0+b1+b2 = 1 mod 3

  (b0%2, b1%2, b2%2) distribution:
